name: serine-type D-Ala-D-Ala carboxypeptidase
reaction: Preferential cleavage: (Ac)2-L-Lys-D-Ala!D-Ala. Also transpeptidation of peptidyl-alanyl moieties that are N-acyl substituents of D-alanine
comment: A membrane-bound, bacterial enzyme inhibited by penicillin and other beta-lactam antibiotics, which acylate the active site serine. Examples are known from peptidase families S11, S12 and S13. Distinct from EC 3.4.17.14, zinc D-Ala-D-Ala carboxypeptidase

references.title: Bacterial wall peptidoglycan, DD-peptidases and beta-lactam antibiotics.
